vigating her own new relationship with Métis comedian Tonya. Legislating Love is a heartwarming play that weaves together past and present in a multi-generational exploration of queer love. It tells the near-forgotten story of one of Canada's quiet heroes and reminds us all that the past must be remembered as we work together for a better future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGay menzCanadavDrama. 7aDRAMA / LGBT.2bisacsh  a1969.  aCalgary.  aEverit Klippert.  aJustin Trudeau apology.  aLGBTQ rights.  aPierre Trudeau.  adecriminalization of homosexuality.  adecriminilization of gay sex.  agay dangerous sexual offender.  agay rights.  agross indecency.  aincurably homosexual.  aincureable homosexuality.  alavender panic.  apride.  aqueer communist panic.  aqueer rights.  athe state has no place in the bedrooms of the people.1 aAllen, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaillie, Tereasa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMehmel, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeisner, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773850825?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773850825423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773850825/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles